Alcan Australia Ltd &lt;AL.S> said it willmake a 39.3 mln N.Z. Dlr cash bid for all the issued shares of&lt;Alcan New Zealand Ltd> at 1.80 N.Z. Dlrs each with afour-for-three share alternative.    Both are 70 pct owned by Canada's Alcan Aluminium Ltd &lt;AL>which will take the share swap option, Alcan Australia deputychairman Jeremy Davis said in a statement. The remainder ofAlcan New Zealand's totalled issued 21.84 mln shares arebroadly held while Alcan Australia's are primarily held byinstitutions. Alcan NZ last traded at 1.55 NZ dlrs, while AlcanAustralia today ended four cents down at 1.15 dlrs.    Davis said the offer, which is subject to approval by theNew Zealand Overseas Investment Commission, was a response tothe integration of the two countries' markets under theAustralia-New Zealand Closer Economic Relations treaty.    Alcan New Zealand shareholders who accept the offer wouldalso receive the final dividend of 10 cents a share normallypayable on May 27.    Alcan Australia would invite New Zealand representation toits board and would apply to list its shares on the New ZealandStock exchange, Davis said. REUTER&#3;